column5: Lets see the items you bought this year at the show, my brother borrowed my camera like last month i should be getting it tomorrow so i will post pics sometime tomorrow.
Picked up a mini Spin Doctor, e chip flasher and an extension for my Scotty rod holder.  You'll have to "visualize", camera is hiding somewhere.

Well  I had a great day at the show . Picked up a new under water camera  and  some new musky lurers . AND also got  a LOWRANCE  332 C fish finder and GPS.  THIS was for a friend. THE  price was right and no TAX .  ALso  looking at a new boat. AT this point it is just looking . ONLY  time will tell if it really happens.  .THE PRICE ON THE CAMERA WAS A GOOD DEAL  ( $ 174 .00  )  CHECK IT OUT ON THERE WEB SITE.   (  www.greentimberoutdoors.com  )

Bly and I were there from about 11am til about 3pm today.  Here's a list of what we came home with....  - OFAH Family Membership (mocked up magazine cover of us holiding a walleye) - 11.5 foot noodle rod (at 40% off) - 2 Baseball hats from Fishing World - A few glass lures from MacKinnon Tackle Inc..makers of the Muskoka Glass Ghost - 2 pairs of polarized sunglasses - some soft bait from "Tightlines"  Not too bad....we figure we spent about 160 bucks at the show.

Manged to hold myself to the 3 for 10 type bins for the most part but picked up some new pliers and a glove at leBarons and a few spoons and spinner baits.  Oh and some buzz baits and some gulp.  Oh and a spare set of glasses.  Oh and some crappie baits and line and ..  ah hell, I'm a sucker for shows like this, I was just happy to keep it under $200.
Heres my pickings from the show this weekend.

Bought a 2 piece med hvy 7 ft st croix musky rod and a glow in the dark thunderstick.  One thing I dlearned is that once company's actions is not the same as another.  This rod was stiffer and rated for heavier line and weight than a heavy action shimano rod of similar specs, very intersting.  They felt very different also, the st croix was much nicer.  Got 2 free hats and a key chain also
- 2 hats from fishing world (me and my dad) - Shimano Baitrunner 4500B (no tax)

I didn't find anything I really wanted at the show but I did walk around for 2hrs getting free samples from all the different smoked meat/sausage vendors.  I can still taste honey garlic venison right now and I was there Saturday
